uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.transition

Interface ViewTransitionFactory<K,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - key type
    T - target type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Contexed, TransitionFactory<K,T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ViewPathTransitionProvider<K,T>, ViewTransitionProvider<K,T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPartTransitionProvider, AbstractViewIndexedTransitionProvider, AbstractViewPathTransitionProvider, AbstractViewTransitionFactory, AbstractViewTransitionProvider, DomTransitionProvider, DynamicFormTransitionProvider, EmailTransitionProvider, PartPathTransitionProvider, PreferenceTransitionProvider, ResponseTransitionProvider, TableTransitionProvider

    public interface ViewTransitionFactory<K,T>
extends TransitionFactory<K,T>
    A TransitionFactory that can use the generic view_target pages. These show a html summary of the object and give buttons to invoke the possible transitions on the target. The view page is shown if no specific transition is requested. This is incompatible with DefaultingTransitionFactory if both interfaces are implemented the view operation will take precedence.
    Author:
    spb
    See Also:
    ViewTransitionProvider, ViewPathTransitionProvider
